data.title: Matt Cameron was in Queens of the Stone Age?
data.meta_description: Ok so on the liner notes for Over the Years and Through the Woods it names the members of Queens and then under it, it read, "Queens have also been:" and it lists Dave Grohl, Nick Oliveri, and Matt Cameron including others.
data.text:
DaytimeDilemma wrote:

Ok so on the liner notes for Over the Years and Through the Woods it names the members of Queens and then under it, it read, "Queens have also been:" and it lists Dave Grohl, Nick Oliveri, and Matt Cameron including others. Was this our Matt Cameron or just someone of the same name?

newwetkojak wrote:

matt cameron ( yes, THE matt cameron) was the original queens of the stone age drummer. actually, they weren't even qotsa yet, they recorded under the name gamma ray. i do know that there is an officially released recording, i think it was a split single with the last kyuss recordings (josh homme's pre-qotsa group). or maybe it was released as gamma ray. shit. i can't believe i don't know for sure or own this motherfucker. 99.99999% sure it was released on frank kozik's "man's ruin" record label. i think van conner from the screaming trees was the bassist at the time too.
